  "prompt": "What do we call video with words on it?",
  "response": "There are several terms you could use to describe a video with words on it, depending on the context and the way the words are presented:\n\n**General terms:**\n\n*   **Text-based video:** This is a broad term that simply means the video prominently features text.\n*   **Video with text overlay:** This describes videos where text is added on top of existing visuals.\n*   **Subtitled video:** If the words are captions or subtitles to translate dialogue.\n*   **Captioned video:** If the words are captions or subtitles to provide accessibility to those who are deaf or hard of hearing.\n\n**More specific terms:**\n\n*   **Kinetic typography video:** If the text is animated and is the primary visual element of the video.\n*   **Lyric video:** If the video displays the lyrics to a song.\n*   **Explainer video:** If the video uses text and graphics to explain a concept.\n*   **Animated infographic:** If the video combines text and animated graphics to present data or information.\n*   **Talking head video with lower thirds:** This describes a video of someone speaking with text at the bottom of the screen providing their name and title.\n\nThe best term to use will depend on the specific characteristics of the video you're describing.\n",
